1
00:00:00,626 --> 00:00:02,085
[♪♪♪]

2
00:00:02,127 --> 00:00:04,296
[footsteps approaching]

3
00:00:10,052 --> 00:00:12,137
[Yamanami]
You two, please wait here.

4
00:00:13,430 --> 00:00:14,932
Listen,

5
00:00:14,973 --> 00:00:17,893
don't move
until you get the signal.

6
00:00:17,976 --> 00:00:21,647
Even if our comrades
are cut down.

7
00:00:23,023 --> 00:00:24,483
Your mission...

8
00:00:25,609 --> 00:00:27,819
is to take
Niimi's head

9
00:00:27,903 --> 00:00:30,322
the moment
the enemy falters.

10
00:00:33,825 --> 00:00:35,494
Soji.
Yes.

11
00:00:36,912 --> 00:00:38,580
Sorry,
but he's mine to kill.

12
00:00:40,207 --> 00:00:41,291
I'd say
it's fair game

13
00:00:41,375 --> 00:00:43,961
for whoever
can land the first strike.

14
00:00:44,044 --> 00:00:46,296
But then again,
I am the fastest one here,

15
00:00:46,338 --> 00:00:47,631
so I'll probably get him.

16
00:00:47,714 --> 00:00:50,342
Don't you get so damn cocky.
[Saito] Yamanami.

17
00:00:52,344 --> 00:00:54,805
[Yamanami]
Oh. Saito.

18
00:00:54,888 --> 00:00:56,390
Position me here, too.

19
00:00:57,808 --> 00:00:59,476
I told you to be
on the front lines.

20
00:00:59,518 --> 00:01:03,105
What difference
does one man make?

21
00:01:03,188 --> 00:01:05,482
That's not for you
to decide.

22
00:01:05,524 --> 00:01:09,111
There are ten of us,
against 150 of them.

23
00:01:10,112 --> 00:01:12,114
Surely you understand

24
00:01:12,197 --> 00:01:15,617
how much every single man
matters.

25
00:01:20,956 --> 00:01:22,249
Please.

26
00:01:25,377 --> 00:01:26,628
Saito.

27
00:01:28,130 --> 00:01:31,675
What is it now?
Trying to hog the spotlight?

28
00:01:31,758 --> 00:01:32,884
[Saito]
That's not it.

29
00:01:34,136 --> 00:01:35,429
I'm the one

30
00:01:37,014 --> 00:01:38,557
who has to kill Niimi.

31
00:01:40,225 --> 00:01:43,353
[♪♪♪]

32
00:01:51,069 --> 00:01:52,654
[Yamanami] But...
Yamanami.

33
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:57,743
On second thought,
I'd rather be on the front line.

34
00:01:57,826 --> 00:01:59,870
[Yamanami]
Hijikata.

35
00:01:59,953 --> 00:02:01,413
When it comes to a fight...

36
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:05,751
it's no fun unless
you're leading the charge.

37
00:02:14,092 --> 00:02:17,387
SONG OF THE SAMURAI

38
00:02:19,973 --> 00:02:21,767
Drop dead! Niimi!

39
00:02:21,850 --> 00:02:23,810
[grunts]

40
00:02:23,894 --> 00:02:25,937
[♪♪♪]

41
00:02:26,021 --> 00:02:27,272
[ronin]
Why you!

42
00:02:54,174 --> 00:02:55,300
[Niimi]
You bastard.

43
00:02:58,136 --> 00:02:59,304
Go!

44
00:03:02,057 --> 00:03:03,308
[shouts]

45
00:03:04,309 --> 00:03:07,187
You're not getting away!

46
00:03:07,270 --> 00:03:09,231
[birds cawing]

47
00:03:11,066 --> 00:03:13,610
[panting]

48
00:03:31,795 --> 00:03:32,838
Agh.

49
00:03:38,719 --> 00:03:39,803
[grunts]

50
00:03:45,225 --> 00:03:48,395
How dare a peon stare at me
while I'm down!

51
00:03:48,478 --> 00:03:53,024
Is it that funny to see a man
groveling on the ground?

52
00:03:57,195 --> 00:03:59,740
[panting]

53
00:04:01,658 --> 00:04:04,578
[♪♪♪]

54
00:04:38,320 --> 00:04:39,905
[rock whooshes, thuds]

55
00:04:42,783 --> 00:04:45,327
[♪♪♪]

56
00:05:14,189 --> 00:05:15,440
[Saito chuckles]

57
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:19,861
You really are a bastard
who's got it coming to him.

58
00:05:21,947 --> 00:05:23,490
Saito.

59
00:05:24,449 --> 00:05:26,451
This is for Eisaburo.

60
00:05:29,371 --> 00:05:31,957
Don't think
you're getting an easy death.

61
00:05:34,125 --> 00:05:36,461
You want to hear
something funny?

62
00:05:37,337 --> 00:05:39,840
Huh?
It's about Abiru.

63
00:05:41,341 --> 00:05:45,929
Don't you wanna know
how he died?

64
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:47,180
[spits]

65
00:05:47,264 --> 00:05:50,725
[laughing]

66
00:05:50,809 --> 00:05:54,271
He was crying.

67
00:05:54,312 --> 00:05:58,149
"I don't wanna die!
I don't wanna die!"

68
00:05:58,233 --> 00:06:00,277
He was a sniveling,
snot-nosed mess,

69
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:02,821
crying like a stuck pig
as he wasted away.

70
00:06:09,202 --> 00:06:10,704
[groans]

71
00:06:20,797 --> 00:06:22,007
[grunting]

72
00:06:30,348 --> 00:06:35,520
Secret Sword,
it's coated in poison!

73
00:06:37,939 --> 00:06:40,859
[laughing]

74
00:06:44,237 --> 00:06:46,031
I see.

75
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:50,452
So that's what it is.

76
00:06:54,539 --> 00:06:57,334
So this is what you used
to kill Eisaburo?

77
00:06:57,417 --> 00:06:59,377
[gasps]

78
00:06:59,461 --> 00:07:01,504
Did you provoke me
to cut your finger

79
00:07:01,588 --> 00:07:03,715
just to make me
let my guard down?

80
00:07:05,300 --> 00:07:07,469
Impossible. How?

81
00:07:07,552 --> 00:07:11,181
When I saw Eisaburo's body,
I knew at first glance.

82
00:07:11,222 --> 00:07:13,475
The wound wasn't deep enough
to be fatal.

83
00:07:13,558 --> 00:07:15,018
But he died
from a single strike,

84
00:07:15,060 --> 00:07:16,353
which could only mean one thing.

85
00:07:16,394 --> 00:07:21,149
That your blade
had to be coated in poison.

86
00:07:21,232 --> 00:07:22,692
You bastard!

87
00:07:22,734 --> 00:07:25,946
You saw through me
from the start?

88
00:07:26,029 --> 00:07:27,572
[screams]

89
00:07:31,159 --> 00:07:33,036
[panting]

90
00:07:33,078 --> 00:07:37,540
Besides, if Eisaburo
had fought you head-on

91
00:07:37,582 --> 00:07:39,793
there's no way he would've
lost to the likes of you!

92
00:07:39,876 --> 00:07:40,877
[spits]
Ugh!

93
00:07:42,963 --> 00:07:45,924
[♪♪♪]

94
00:07:46,925 --> 00:07:49,636
[thunder cracking]
[coughing]

95
00:08:23,545 --> 00:08:26,423
I won. I won!

96
00:08:26,506 --> 00:08:28,508
Bye, you dumb runts.

97
00:08:28,591 --> 00:08:31,678
I swear I'll make you pay
for this!

98
00:08:35,015 --> 00:08:36,975
[groaning]

99
00:08:45,400 --> 00:08:48,111
[groaning frantically]

100
00:08:56,619 --> 00:08:59,289
You have a surprisingly
short memory.

101
00:09:00,623 --> 00:09:02,000
I'm sure I told you.

102
00:09:03,168 --> 00:09:06,880
"Don't think you're getting
an easy death."

103
00:09:06,963 --> 00:09:09,132
All right!

104
00:09:09,174 --> 00:09:11,176
I... I lose!

105
00:09:13,636 --> 00:09:15,555
So I'm begging you!

106
00:09:15,638 --> 00:09:19,184
Look... my finger's been cut.

107
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,977
My leg's been slashed.

108
00:09:22,103 --> 00:09:23,354
With these injuries,

109
00:09:23,438 --> 00:09:26,232
I'll never be able
to hold a sword again.

110
00:09:26,316 --> 00:09:31,946
Please, just spare my life!

111
00:09:35,575 --> 00:09:37,285
Of course, considering
everything I've done...

112
00:09:37,327 --> 00:09:42,957
I know it's selfish
of me to ask.

113
00:09:43,041 --> 00:09:44,000
That's why...!

114
00:09:58,473 --> 00:10:01,810
[screaming]

115
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:16,324
[screaming]

116
00:10:21,579 --> 00:10:24,666
[whimpering]

117
00:10:24,749 --> 00:10:29,003
Is this...
enough for you to forgive me?

118
00:10:34,592 --> 00:10:36,594
You want to live that badly?

119
00:10:36,678 --> 00:10:38,429
[Niimi sniveling]

120
00:10:38,513 --> 00:10:40,181
You're truly pathetic.

121
00:10:41,933 --> 00:10:44,435
[sobbing]

122
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,358
Forget it.

123
00:10:52,694 --> 00:10:54,112
You just killed it for me.

124
00:10:57,157 --> 00:10:58,908
[gasps]

125
00:10:58,950 --> 00:11:00,577
You mean it?

126
00:11:00,660 --> 00:11:03,204
Yeah. Just get lost.

127
00:11:06,457 --> 00:11:08,751
[sniveling]

128
00:11:12,463 --> 00:11:14,257
I won.

129
00:11:14,340 --> 00:11:16,301
[Saito]
You thought you won?

130
00:11:16,384 --> 00:11:17,302
Huh?

131
00:11:22,265 --> 00:11:24,767
[thunder cracking]

132
00:11:34,068 --> 00:11:37,572
[screams]

133
00:11:37,655 --> 00:11:40,783
[♪♪♪]

134
00:11:44,078 --> 00:11:45,747
Niimi Nishiki.

135
00:11:49,083 --> 00:11:51,878
I was the only one
who forgave you.

136
00:11:54,339 --> 00:11:57,175
But the one you really need
forgiveness from...

137
00:11:58,801 --> 00:12:00,929
isn't here, unfortunately.

138
00:12:03,848 --> 00:12:07,185
Go ask him for forgiveness
yourself in the afterlife.

139
00:12:31,668 --> 00:12:35,171
[narrator]
Niimi Nishiki's betrayal
was never made public.

140
00:12:35,213 --> 00:12:38,883
Instead, the cover story
was that he committed seppuku

141
00:12:38,967 --> 00:12:40,510
for unauthorized fundraising.

142
00:12:46,933 --> 00:12:50,561
Here, Eisaburo.
I'm returning it to you.

143
00:12:54,899 --> 00:12:57,068
Your brother's keepsake.

144
00:13:02,699 --> 00:13:04,409
Now you can finally
get some sleep.

145
00:13:21,718 --> 00:13:23,886
[sighs]

146
00:13:23,970 --> 00:13:26,973
In the end,
maybe he helped me beat Niimi.

147
00:13:28,808 --> 00:13:30,101
[Hijikata]
Oh.

148
00:13:32,937 --> 00:13:35,398
But Hajime buddy...

149
00:13:35,481 --> 00:13:36,566
Hajime buddy?

150
00:13:39,027 --> 00:13:40,361
Don't you forget this.

151
00:13:43,323 --> 00:13:47,577
Back there, I could've easily
taken the shot at Niimi myself.

152
00:13:48,911 --> 00:13:50,955
But I saw what you wanted

153
00:13:51,039 --> 00:13:52,582
so I reluctantly
let you have him.

154
00:13:52,665 --> 00:13:55,626
Listen up! You only got to
take Niimi down because of me!

155
00:13:55,710 --> 00:13:58,880
[chuckling]
Toshi, you're the same as ever.
Saying something so stupid...

156
00:13:58,963 --> 00:14:01,758
What's so stupid about it?
I almost have to respect it.

157
00:14:01,799 --> 00:14:03,760
Hey, Eisaburo,
are you watching this?

158
00:14:03,843 --> 00:14:05,345
Toshi's an idiot, as always.

159
00:14:05,428 --> 00:14:07,930
Hey, takes one to know one,
you idiot.
[laughing]

160
00:14:07,972 --> 00:14:10,016
Right, Eisaburo?
"Takes one to know one"?

161
00:14:10,099 --> 00:14:12,977
Me, an idiot?
Just watch
and see who the real idiot is.

162
00:14:13,061 --> 00:14:15,229
Come on, just watch, Eisaburo.
It's obviously Toshi.

163
00:14:15,313 --> 00:14:16,481
Hey you!

164
00:14:16,564 --> 00:14:18,107
[grunting sigh]

165
00:14:20,943 --> 00:14:25,740
Aijiro, I guess the next time
we train...

166
00:14:25,823 --> 00:14:27,450
will be in the afterlife.

167
00:14:29,619 --> 00:14:35,041
Until then, keep an eye on me,
even though I'm talentless.

168
00:14:42,340 --> 00:14:45,385
I see, I see.
So Niimi has fallen.

169
00:14:47,428 --> 00:14:50,807
He was a tragic figure
in his own way.

170
00:14:50,848 --> 00:14:53,142
Explain yourself,
Yamazaki.

171
00:14:53,226 --> 00:14:57,146
You said Kondo's group was less
than ten men strong, right?

172
00:14:59,023 --> 00:15:02,110
So how the hell did they beat
Niimi and his 150 men?!

173
00:15:03,486 --> 00:15:05,571
Winning and losing
is a matter of luck.

174
00:15:05,655 --> 00:15:07,657
Not my department.

175
00:15:07,698 --> 00:15:09,992
[Serizawa grunts]

176
00:15:10,076 --> 00:15:11,994
Niimi was your master,
wasn't he?

177
00:15:12,078 --> 00:15:13,579
Don't you feel
any remorse?

178
00:15:13,663 --> 00:15:15,081
Money!

179
00:15:16,874 --> 00:15:18,042
Remorse?

180
00:15:19,043 --> 00:15:21,712
Can't exactly eat remorse,
can you?

181
00:15:21,796 --> 00:15:24,006
[laughs]

182
00:15:24,090 --> 00:15:28,219
You're rotten to the core.
Can't say I dislike it, though.

183
00:15:28,302 --> 00:15:30,012
Money!

184
00:15:30,054 --> 00:15:31,722
I'll take that
as a compliment.

185
00:15:35,768 --> 00:15:38,396
So, what's our move,
Master Serizawa?

186
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:41,274
Now, most of our men
will flock to their side.

187
00:15:41,357 --> 00:15:42,483
Hirayama...

188
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:49,282
What I've always wanted is an
all-out war, no tricks. Got it?

189
00:15:49,365 --> 00:15:50,408
Hm.

190
00:15:51,909 --> 00:15:53,453
Of course, I understand.

191
00:15:54,912 --> 00:15:56,414
But...

192
00:15:58,332 --> 00:16:00,543
We need more fuel for the fire.
Yeah.

193
00:16:00,626 --> 00:16:02,086
[chuckles]

194
00:16:06,632 --> 00:16:07,592
Start.

195
00:16:11,846 --> 00:16:15,641
Oh? Goro, you've gotten sloppy.

196
00:16:15,725 --> 00:16:17,518
Ichiji! You bastard!

197
00:16:17,602 --> 00:16:19,312
[♪♪♪]

198
00:16:19,395 --> 00:16:21,105
[laughter]

199
00:16:21,189 --> 00:16:22,440
[Hirayama]
Niji, you're here too?

200
00:16:22,523 --> 00:16:24,233
What's with that look
on your face?

201
00:16:24,317 --> 00:16:27,069
[laughing]
You got a problem
with us being here?

202
00:16:27,153 --> 00:16:28,529
[Hirayama]
Yeah, I do.

203
00:16:28,571 --> 00:16:30,990
We're the guys who raised hell
in Mito, aren't we?

204
00:16:31,073 --> 00:16:34,076
[Serizawa]
Okay, everyone's here.

205
00:16:34,160 --> 00:16:37,288
So, Kamo.
So, who's first?

206
00:16:38,164 --> 00:16:39,916
You wouldn't have called us

207
00:16:39,957 --> 00:16:41,626
unless it was
for someone big, right?

208
00:16:41,709 --> 00:16:42,877
Hm.

209
00:16:42,960 --> 00:16:45,171
[gasps]
I know. The Shogun!

210
00:16:45,254 --> 00:16:47,423
Whoa, you want to go after
Lord Iemochi?

211
00:16:47,507 --> 00:16:49,175
Still a dumbass, I see.

212
00:16:51,302 --> 00:16:54,263
[gasping]

213
00:16:54,305 --> 00:16:56,891
Ichiji!
Goro just called me a dumbass!

214
00:16:56,974 --> 00:16:58,976
Hey! The one who calls someone
a dumbass is the real dumbass!

215
00:16:59,060 --> 00:17:00,186
Dumbass. Dumbass.

216
00:17:00,269 --> 00:17:04,106
Goro, don't get too cocky.

217
00:17:04,148 --> 00:17:06,484
[booger splats]
Huh?

218
00:17:06,567 --> 00:17:10,112
You're supposed to be
his right-hand man

219
00:17:10,154 --> 00:17:13,115
so why hasn't Kamo
taken over the world yet?!

220
00:17:13,199 --> 00:17:15,117
See?
Goro's the real dumbass!

221
00:17:15,159 --> 00:17:16,452
Shut up, you dumbass.

222
00:17:16,494 --> 00:17:18,246
Want me to crush you
right here and now?!

223
00:17:18,329 --> 00:17:21,165
Come on, come on!
What a lively bunch.

224
00:17:22,250 --> 00:17:24,460
The reason I called you here
is simple.

225
00:17:24,502 --> 00:17:26,837
The stage is finally set
to my liking.

226
00:17:26,921 --> 00:17:29,423
I intend to enjoy
every last second of it.

227
00:17:29,507 --> 00:17:30,716
Hmm...

228
00:17:30,800 --> 00:17:32,969
[♪♪♪]

229
00:17:33,010 --> 00:17:38,224
You all get it, don't you?
What I'm getting at.

230
00:17:41,644 --> 00:17:42,812
[chuckles]

231
00:17:44,939 --> 00:17:46,774
Unleash
your overwhelming violence

232
00:17:46,857 --> 00:17:48,234
and trample all over Kyo.

233
00:17:50,861 --> 00:17:53,948
[Saito, laughing]
Awesome!

234
00:17:54,031 --> 00:17:55,366
[Nagakura]
Here they come.

235
00:17:56,534 --> 00:17:58,286
[chuckling]

236
00:18:05,126 --> 00:18:07,253
Serizawa Kamo is on the move.

237
00:18:08,296 --> 00:18:10,089
[Yamanami]
He's gathered new allies

238
00:18:10,172 --> 00:18:12,258
and appears
to be plotting something.

239
00:18:13,509 --> 00:18:15,011
[sighs]

240
00:18:15,052 --> 00:18:19,682
What on earth
is that man planning to do?

241
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:21,767
I have no idea whatsoever.

242
00:18:23,269 --> 00:18:24,812
All we know is...

243
00:18:27,565 --> 00:18:28,774
Please, go ahead.

244
00:18:30,109 --> 00:18:31,986
Yamanami, who did
you say that to?

245
00:18:32,069 --> 00:18:34,905
[Yamazaki, imitating Serizawa]
The reason I called you here
is simple.

246
00:18:34,989 --> 00:18:36,782
I intend to enjoy
every last second of it.

247
00:18:36,866 --> 00:18:38,367
You all get it, don't you?
What I'm getting at.

248
00:18:38,451 --> 00:18:40,202
[Hijikata]
This voice... Is it Kamo?

249
00:18:40,244 --> 00:18:42,288
[Yamazaki]
Unleash your
overwhelming violence

250
00:18:42,371 --> 00:18:43,748
and trample all over Kyo.

251
00:18:47,543 --> 00:18:49,754
[slides]

252
00:18:51,380 --> 00:18:53,049
[Todo]
Yamazaki, you bastard!

253
00:18:53,132 --> 00:18:54,467
I thought you were
on Niimi's side.

254
00:18:54,550 --> 00:18:57,219
[Yamanami]
He's not on anyone's side.

255
00:18:57,261 --> 00:19:00,931
He'll do anything
for the right price.

256
00:19:01,015 --> 00:19:03,434
He's the one
who spread that rumor for us

257
00:19:03,517 --> 00:19:06,437
about Kondo
and Lord Katamori's meeting.

258
00:19:09,023 --> 00:19:11,275
[Nagakura]
So he's a double agent.

259
00:19:11,359 --> 00:19:14,111
[Yamazaki, normally]
Mm. Something like that.

260
00:19:14,195 --> 00:19:16,781
My loyalty lies
with the highest bidder.

261
00:19:16,864 --> 00:19:20,910
[laughs]
Playing both sides
for double the pay, huh?

262
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:23,579
You're a special kind
of scumbag.

263
00:19:23,663 --> 00:19:25,373
Why, thank you.

264
00:19:28,626 --> 00:19:29,877
[Kondo sighs]

265
00:19:31,420 --> 00:19:35,299
Serizawa Kamo
wants a piece of us.

266
00:19:37,843 --> 00:19:39,804
The real fight starts now.

267
00:19:47,353 --> 00:19:49,146
[pedestrian 1]
Oh, it's beautiful.

268
00:19:49,230 --> 00:19:50,981
[pedestrian 2]
It is beautiful.

269
00:19:51,065 --> 00:19:52,608
[narrator]
At this time, another power

270
00:19:52,692 --> 00:19:55,277
was beginning to make its mark
on Kyo: the Satsuma clan

271
00:19:55,361 --> 00:19:59,532
a powerhouse from western
provinces, allied with Aizu.

272
00:20:00,700 --> 00:20:02,827
[blade slices]
[man screams, groaning]

273
00:20:02,910 --> 00:20:05,663
What happened? Are you okay?

274
00:20:05,746 --> 00:20:08,124
[♪♪♪]

275
00:20:08,207 --> 00:20:09,333
Are you okay?

276
00:20:09,417 --> 00:20:12,420
Are you okay? Hey! Hey!

277
00:20:34,191 --> 00:20:35,985
That Haori jacket...

278
00:20:36,026 --> 00:20:37,987
Are you with
the Shinsengumi?

279
00:20:38,028 --> 00:20:39,822
That accent...

280
00:20:39,864 --> 00:20:42,575
They're from Satsuma,
no doubt about it.

281
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:43,826
Yep.

282
00:20:44,952 --> 00:20:46,412
What do you want?

283
00:20:47,371 --> 00:20:49,957
You're with the Aizu clan!

284
00:20:49,999 --> 00:20:51,500
And we of Satsuma
and the Aizu are...

285
00:20:51,584 --> 00:20:53,586
[blood splattering]
[groaning]

286
00:20:56,881 --> 00:21:00,050
Less talking, more fighting,
or you'll end up dead.

287
00:21:00,134 --> 00:21:03,345
[Satsuma retainer]
You're blocking our patrol.
Step aside!

288
00:21:03,387 --> 00:21:06,849
[laughing]
I can't understand
a damn word he's saying.

289
00:21:06,891 --> 00:21:09,018
Bunch of potato samurai.

290
00:21:10,186 --> 00:21:11,604
What did you say?!

291
00:21:12,396 --> 00:21:14,190
Uh-oh, the potato's angry.

292
00:21:14,273 --> 00:21:16,025
I'm scared, Ichiji.

293
00:21:16,066 --> 00:21:19,361
Bastard!
Don't you dare insult Satsuma!

294
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:21,655
Get them!
Cut them down!

295
00:21:21,739 --> 00:21:23,741
Just what you'd expect
from Satsuma.

296
00:21:23,824 --> 00:21:25,951
So quick to fight.
Saves us the trouble.

297
00:21:27,995 --> 00:21:31,540
Niji! That's the Jigen style.

298
00:21:31,582 --> 00:21:33,417
Hiyah!

299
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:37,296
[grunting]

300
00:21:43,260 --> 00:21:46,430
Scary...
So scary, scary, scary...

301
00:21:49,099 --> 00:21:52,019
It's all right.
Niji, you are capable.

302
00:21:52,102 --> 00:21:53,729
Have some confidence.

303
00:21:53,771 --> 00:21:55,689
Hiyaa!

304
00:21:55,773 --> 00:21:57,691
Kill, Niji!

305
00:22:00,486 --> 00:22:03,656
Okay, I get it, Ichiji!

306
00:22:03,739 --> 00:22:05,032
Hiya!

307
00:22:10,621 --> 00:22:11,789
Hiya!

308
00:22:13,207 --> 00:22:14,458
[exclaims]

309
00:22:27,179 --> 00:22:29,431
That was so scary.

310
00:22:30,558 --> 00:22:33,394
Jigen style... Piece of cake.

311
00:22:34,520 --> 00:22:36,647
[Satsuma retainer]
What's their deal?

312
00:22:40,109 --> 00:22:44,280
[footsteps crunching loudly]

313
00:22:44,321 --> 00:22:47,658
Everyone, step back.

314
00:22:53,163 --> 00:22:57,001
[♪♪♪]

315
00:23:01,338 --> 00:23:04,133
Ichiji, that guy's eyes
are terrifying.

316
00:23:04,216 --> 00:23:05,426
Who are you?

317
00:23:07,011 --> 00:23:11,557
Why is the Shinsengumi
attacking Satsuma?

318
00:23:12,725 --> 00:23:15,561
Ichiji? His eyes are scary!

319
00:23:17,646 --> 00:23:20,733
Too much trouble.
You don't have to answer.

320
00:23:25,613 --> 00:23:27,823
Hanjiro! You aren't
planning to do that...

321
00:23:27,865 --> 00:23:29,116
Hanjiro?

322
00:23:32,453 --> 00:23:36,707
SATSUMA RETAINER,
NAKAMURA HANJIRO

323
00:23:40,377 --> 00:23:42,254
This is awesome!

324
00:23:42,338 --> 00:23:45,466
I've been dying
to see the real thing!

325
00:23:45,549 --> 00:23:47,801
Right, Niji?
You're right, Ichiji!

326
00:23:47,885 --> 00:23:49,011
Let's go!

327
00:23:49,053 --> 00:23:51,180
[both yelling]
Fall!

328
00:23:57,519 --> 00:23:59,229
[groaning]

329
00:24:03,484 --> 00:24:05,653
[creaking]

330
00:24:10,616 --> 00:24:14,328
[crying]
Ow! Ichiji! He cut me!

331
00:24:14,411 --> 00:24:16,705
Damn, what incredible power...

332
00:24:17,831 --> 00:24:19,458
I see.

333
00:24:19,541 --> 00:24:22,419
So you're Hanjiro the Manslayer,
huh?

334
00:24:22,503 --> 00:24:25,005
[Niji]
What? Is that right, Ichiji?

335
00:24:26,256 --> 00:24:28,217
Even though
it was two against one,

336
00:24:28,300 --> 00:24:30,386
you actually landed a hit on me?

337
00:24:30,427 --> 00:24:32,930
Who the hell are you guys?

338
00:24:34,765 --> 00:24:38,060
[Satsuma retainer]
Hey! Hurry! Over here!

339
00:24:39,937 --> 00:24:41,647
It's Shinsengumi!

340
00:24:42,940 --> 00:24:45,609
Looks like we both
cheated death today.

341
00:24:45,693 --> 00:24:50,114
I swear,
I'm going to kill both of you.

342
00:24:51,198 --> 00:24:52,574
[scoffs]

343
00:24:52,616 --> 00:24:54,576
Let's get out of here, Niji.

344
00:24:54,660 --> 00:24:55,744
They are coming!

345
00:24:55,786 --> 00:25:00,624
Hey! Get them! After them!

346
00:25:00,708 --> 00:25:03,585
[indistinct shouting]

347
00:25:05,129 --> 00:25:06,672
Whoo!

348
00:25:06,755 --> 00:25:08,757
Kyo sure is wild!
[laughing]

349
00:25:08,841 --> 00:25:11,635
If more of them show up,
we won't make it.

350
00:25:11,719 --> 00:25:14,638
What do we do? Niji!

351
00:25:15,639 --> 00:25:19,560
It was scary, but fun too,
wasn't it?

352
00:25:19,643 --> 00:25:22,730
[both laughing]

353
00:25:22,813 --> 00:25:24,732
After them!
Hey! Hold it!

354
00:25:24,815 --> 00:25:29,820
Get them! Hey!
Get them!

355
00:25:30,863 --> 00:25:32,448
Hey!

356
00:25:32,489 --> 00:25:34,199
Ooh!

357
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:35,826
[groans]

358
00:25:41,498 --> 00:25:42,916
[arrows thwacking]

359
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,586
[laughing]

360
00:25:49,882 --> 00:25:51,759
[Satsuma retainer]
Wait.

361
00:25:53,093 --> 00:25:54,928
I said, wait.

362
00:25:59,058 --> 00:26:03,937
[Sagawa]
The perpetrators appear
to be from the Shinsengumi.

363
00:26:04,021 --> 00:26:06,231
The Shinsengumi?

364
00:26:06,315 --> 00:26:07,608
Yes, my lord!

365
00:26:07,691 --> 00:26:09,485
Three men
attacked Satsuma samurai,

366
00:26:09,568 --> 00:26:12,196
reportedly wearing
their striped haori.

367
00:26:14,156 --> 00:26:16,617
I wondered
how they would play this...

368
00:26:17,826 --> 00:26:20,162
So that's
how they're going to play it.

369
00:26:20,245 --> 00:26:22,581
They may be allied
with the Aizu clan for now,

370
00:26:22,664 --> 00:26:26,710
but ultimately Satsuma is
still an outside domain.

371
00:26:26,794 --> 00:26:30,714
Sooner or later, they will
turn against the Shogunate.

372
00:26:34,843 --> 00:26:36,887
What are your orders?

373
00:26:42,017 --> 00:26:43,060
Kanbei.

374
00:26:44,103 --> 00:26:45,187
[Sagawa]
Yes, my lord!

375
00:26:46,980 --> 00:26:49,233
Relay this to Kamo and Kondo.

376
00:26:50,359 --> 00:26:52,319
To settle this score

377
00:26:53,821 --> 00:26:55,948
one of their heads
will have to roll.

378
00:26:57,908 --> 00:27:00,536
[Sagawa]
Yes, my lord! At once!

379
00:27:00,577 --> 00:27:03,038
[footsteps departing]

380
00:27:03,122 --> 00:27:06,667
[♪♪♪]

381
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:08,001
[sucks teeth]

382
00:27:10,045 --> 00:27:11,380
Well, hello there.

383
00:27:12,756 --> 00:27:15,425
Enjoy.
Welcome, sir. Welcome.

384
00:27:21,849 --> 00:27:25,936
[Oume]
Mr. Sagawa,
your guest has arrived.

385
00:27:27,104 --> 00:27:28,105
Yes.

386
00:27:35,571 --> 00:27:39,700
[heavy footsteps approaching]

387
00:27:42,786 --> 00:27:44,538
[Serizawa, chuckles]
What's the matter?

388
00:27:44,621 --> 00:27:47,416
Missing the smell
of face powder?

389
00:27:47,457 --> 00:27:49,376
I can't believe
you actually came.

390
00:27:49,459 --> 00:27:52,629
I can't exactly say no
when Oume's the one asking.

391
00:27:52,713 --> 00:27:56,049
[sighs]
Thanks for setting this up.

392
00:27:56,925 --> 00:27:58,260
There isn't a soul here

393
00:27:58,343 --> 00:27:59,803
who doesn't know about you two.

394
00:27:59,887 --> 00:28:02,514
Did you never think
I was gathering men

395
00:28:02,598 --> 00:28:05,058
to capture Serizawa?

396
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:10,772
I've seen many men
in my line of work

397
00:28:10,814 --> 00:28:15,068
so I can read a man's
true intentions in his eyes.

398
00:28:18,447 --> 00:28:22,075
Well then,
if you'll excuse me.

399
00:28:25,412 --> 00:28:30,334
She's quite a woman, huh?
So, what do you want, Kanbei?

400
00:28:30,417 --> 00:28:32,628
The Satsuma clan was attacked.

401
00:28:32,711 --> 00:28:34,254
[sighs]

402
00:28:34,338 --> 00:28:36,798
Over a dozen of their men
were cut down,

403
00:28:36,882 --> 00:28:38,967
and Nakamura Hanjiro
was wounded too.

404
00:28:39,051 --> 00:28:42,387
Oh? Someone managed to wound the
great Hanjiro the Manslayer, eh?

405
00:28:42,471 --> 00:28:44,848
Vast though Kyo may be,
the men with that skill

406
00:28:44,932 --> 00:28:47,184
can be counted on one hand.

407
00:28:47,267 --> 00:28:48,769
[clattering]

408
00:28:48,852 --> 00:28:52,356
So you think I did it.
Is that it?

409
00:28:54,942 --> 00:28:56,860
Coming here to accuse me...

410
00:28:56,944 --> 00:29:00,155
you'd better be ready
for the consequences.

411
00:29:02,449 --> 00:29:03,951
Ah.

412
00:29:10,749 --> 00:29:12,251
[chuckling]
Just kidding.

413
00:29:12,334 --> 00:29:14,503
Still can't get a rise
out of you, can I?

414
00:29:14,586 --> 00:29:17,047
You're right on the money.
Yup.

415
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:18,382
So it was you.

416
00:29:19,508 --> 00:29:20,968
But why?

417
00:29:21,009 --> 00:29:24,846
Now we of Aizu have no choice
but to cut you down.

418
00:29:24,888 --> 00:29:26,139
And that's not all.

419
00:29:26,223 --> 00:29:29,017
The Satsuma men
are coming at you full force.

420
00:29:29,059 --> 00:29:32,229
Well, that's because
I engineered it that way.

421
00:29:33,647 --> 00:29:35,065
I don't understand.

422
00:29:36,066 --> 00:29:38,068
Why are you
in such a rush to die?

423
00:29:39,194 --> 00:29:40,195
Hey, Kanbei...

424
00:29:40,237 --> 00:29:41,571
[smacks lips]

425
00:29:41,655 --> 00:29:42,948
I've been wanting to ask

426
00:29:43,031 --> 00:29:45,242
the greatest samurai
in Japan something...

427
00:29:45,951 --> 00:29:47,828
What is a samurai?

428
00:29:47,911 --> 00:29:51,498
[scoffs]
Of all the things to ask.

429
00:29:54,501 --> 00:29:57,212
They serve their lord
with loyalty and martial prowess

430
00:29:57,296 --> 00:29:59,548
and lay down their lives
for their lord

431
00:29:59,631 --> 00:30:01,216
without a second thought.

432
00:30:01,300 --> 00:30:03,343
That is what it means
to be a samurai.

433
00:30:03,427 --> 00:30:04,803
[laughs]

434
00:30:04,886 --> 00:30:08,390
Loyalty like that makes you
a fool in this day and age.

435
00:30:08,432 --> 00:30:10,225
But listen.
[sniffs]

436
00:30:12,728 --> 00:30:15,355
Don't give me
that idealistic crap, Kanbei.

437
00:30:16,815 --> 00:30:19,901
I'm sure you know it
in your gut.

438
00:30:19,985 --> 00:30:22,070
Ultimately,
samurai are just thugs

439
00:30:22,154 --> 00:30:24,448
who only know
a life of violence.

440
00:30:26,575 --> 00:30:29,578
Then let's bloom
as wildly as we can.

441
00:30:29,661 --> 00:30:31,163
Until we fall.

442
00:30:36,084 --> 00:30:39,296
[Hijikata, sighing]
What is that bastard Kamo
playing at?

443
00:30:39,379 --> 00:30:43,091
Is he trying to take down
both us and Aizu?

444
00:30:43,133 --> 00:30:45,010
[Shimada]
Why would he be so reckless...?

445
00:30:45,093 --> 00:30:47,721
[Kondo]
He just wants
to fan the flames, right?

446
00:30:47,804 --> 00:30:51,933
[Sasaki]
Well, I don't really care why

447
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:56,521
I'm just here to deliver
an order from Lord Katamori.

448
00:30:59,941 --> 00:31:02,778
To make amends for this,

449
00:31:02,819 --> 00:31:05,405
we require the head
of either Kondo

450
00:31:05,489 --> 00:31:07,366
or Serizawa.

451
00:31:09,743 --> 00:31:10,994
[Todo]
Why Kondo's head?!

452
00:31:11,078 --> 00:31:13,955
That bastard Kamo
is the one who did it!

453
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:14,998
This is insane!

454
00:31:15,082 --> 00:31:16,917
His Lordship
knows full well.

455
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:19,044
Then why...

456
00:31:25,884 --> 00:31:30,138
If we are defeated,
I will offer up my head.

457
00:31:31,890 --> 00:31:35,268
Anything less will not appease
Satsuma's wrath.

458
00:31:35,352 --> 00:31:38,522
[♪♪♪]

459
00:31:40,690 --> 00:31:43,443
[Sasaki]
Settle this, and quickly.

460
00:32:15,100 --> 00:32:16,268
[Kondo]
Soji.

461
00:32:18,395 --> 00:32:19,479
Let's spar.

462
00:32:21,356 --> 00:32:22,441
Kondo...

463
00:32:37,914 --> 00:32:39,583
[exhales]

464
00:32:41,209 --> 00:32:42,377
Soji.

465
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,006
Not getting any funny ideas,
are you?

466
00:32:55,474 --> 00:32:58,101
I can't fool you,
can I, Kondo?

467
00:33:04,274 --> 00:33:06,276
Hijikata won't like this, but...

468
00:33:07,319 --> 00:33:09,321
I'll be the one
to kill Serizawa.

469
00:33:10,447 --> 00:33:11,323
Soji.

470
00:33:11,406 --> 00:33:14,409
Don't worry, Kondo.
I'll be fine.

471
00:33:17,078 --> 00:33:20,290
I won't lose myself again.

472
00:34:25,814 --> 00:34:28,692
[screams]

473
00:34:30,652 --> 00:34:31,903
[sobbing]

474
00:34:31,987 --> 00:34:33,196
[Serizawa]
Hey.

475
00:34:33,280 --> 00:34:36,408
[footsteps approaching slowly]

476
00:34:39,077 --> 00:34:42,414
Hey, what's wrong?
Why the long face?

477
00:34:45,041 --> 00:34:46,376
Hey, Kamo.

478
00:34:47,460 --> 00:34:49,838
What the hell
are you doing here?

479
00:34:49,879 --> 00:34:53,800
I had a feeling
you were calling for me.

480
00:34:53,883 --> 00:34:55,677
Don't screw with me!

481
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:56,803
[laughs]

482
00:34:56,886 --> 00:34:59,306
What's got you
so worked up? Huh?

483
00:34:59,389 --> 00:35:01,308
Why did you attack
Satsuma?

484
00:35:02,559 --> 00:35:04,686
I thought
you wanted to fight us.

485
00:35:04,728 --> 00:35:06,313
Hm.

486
00:35:06,396 --> 00:35:08,857
You sold out Niimi for that,
didn't you?

487
00:35:11,109 --> 00:35:13,862
The bigger the fire,
the better, right?

488
00:35:15,405 --> 00:35:18,408
You make no sense,
as usual.

489
00:35:21,244 --> 00:35:23,830
What? You really don't get it?

490
00:35:25,081 --> 00:35:28,209
No, I don't.
You should understand.

491
00:35:28,251 --> 00:35:31,171
That urge
to leap into a raging fire.

492
00:35:33,965 --> 00:35:39,679
Don't give me that crap.
Unlike you,

493
00:35:39,763 --> 00:35:42,599
I won't abandon my comrades
and throw my life away.

494
00:35:42,682 --> 00:35:46,186
[Serizawa]
Then why do you want to kill me?

495
00:35:46,269 --> 00:35:48,855
For the Shinsengumi?
For your comrades?

496
00:35:48,938 --> 00:35:50,440
No, that's not it, is it?

497
00:35:52,359 --> 00:35:56,237
Even you must see it...
Where this era is headed.

498
00:35:56,321 --> 00:35:58,448
The end of the samurai.

499
00:36:02,952 --> 00:36:04,454
[Serizawa chuckles]

500
00:36:08,333 --> 00:36:11,628
So in an age like this,
why did you become a samurai?

501
00:36:11,711 --> 00:36:13,171
Hm?

502
00:36:15,965 --> 00:36:17,842
Blood.

503
00:36:17,926 --> 00:36:19,469
Yeah.

504
00:36:21,638 --> 00:36:23,264
Because fighting
a strong opponent

505
00:36:23,348 --> 00:36:24,808
makes my blood boil.

506
00:36:26,059 --> 00:36:30,355
It's the only time I feel alive.

507
00:36:30,438 --> 00:36:33,733
I feel the same.
Then draw.

508
00:36:35,235 --> 00:36:36,861
I want to be stronger.

509
00:36:36,945 --> 00:36:38,279
To think of nothing else,

510
00:36:38,321 --> 00:36:40,532
to challenge opponents
stronger than you

511
00:36:40,615 --> 00:36:42,742
to reach greater heights
with the sword.

512
00:36:42,826 --> 00:36:45,829
That's the only way I can live.
But...

513
00:36:48,415 --> 00:36:50,667
what lies at the end
of that path?

514
00:36:52,627 --> 00:36:53,712
Huh?

515
00:36:58,675 --> 00:37:01,886
[♪♪♪]

516
00:37:01,970 --> 00:37:03,847
Death.

517
00:37:06,224 --> 00:37:08,560
I've already
made my peace with that.

518
00:37:10,186 --> 00:37:11,855
The weak die.

519
00:37:13,231 --> 00:37:14,816
That's all there is to it.

520
00:37:14,899 --> 00:37:16,317
That's right. Exactly.

521
00:37:16,359 --> 00:37:18,695
A man can't choose
how he's born.

522
00:37:20,113 --> 00:37:22,907
But he can decide
how he dies.

523
00:37:25,744 --> 00:37:27,454
That's why...

524
00:37:28,580 --> 00:37:30,415
from the moment
I was born,

525
00:37:30,498 --> 00:37:33,251
I have sought
only one thing.

526
00:37:35,587 --> 00:37:40,300
How I will meet my end.
Nothing more.

527
00:37:42,677 --> 00:37:43,762
[chuckles softly]

528
00:37:45,096 --> 00:37:46,890
You've realized it too,
haven't you?

529
00:37:48,266 --> 00:37:50,977
You and I are two sides
of the same coin.

530
00:37:51,978 --> 00:37:53,062
We're light and shadow.

531
00:37:53,146 --> 00:37:55,648
Men who only feel alive
in battle.

532
00:37:57,650 --> 00:38:00,111
It's no coincidence we met.

533
00:38:00,195 --> 00:38:02,530
Our very souls
are drawn to each other.

534
00:38:02,614 --> 00:38:03,907
[chuckles]

535
00:38:10,580 --> 00:38:14,167
Dead of night.
At Sumiya, in Shimabara.

536
00:38:14,250 --> 00:38:16,044
Don't keep me waiting.

537
00:38:21,382 --> 00:38:22,926
Bring it on.

538
00:38:24,302 --> 00:38:28,431
[♪♪♪]

539
00:38:32,769 --> 00:38:35,063
[Yamanami]
Right now, Serizawa is...

540
00:38:36,606 --> 00:38:40,735
at the Sumiya in Shimabara,
with his mistress, Oume.

541
00:38:44,405 --> 00:38:47,659
That's correct, isn't it?
Yamazaki?

542
00:38:50,453 --> 00:38:53,540
[board clattering]

543
00:38:53,623 --> 00:38:55,583
[Yamazaki] Yes.
[Todo] There you are.

544
00:38:55,625 --> 00:38:59,587
[Yamazaki]
In addition,
I have intel that Serizawa's men

545
00:38:59,671 --> 00:39:02,590
plan to attack
our headquarters tonight.

546
00:39:02,632 --> 00:39:04,092
Their target is, of course

547
00:39:05,552 --> 00:39:07,637
Kondo Isami's head.

548
00:39:14,978 --> 00:39:16,813
[Yamanami]
Here is my plan.

549
00:39:17,647 --> 00:39:20,692
We'll launch a preemptive strike

550
00:39:20,775 --> 00:39:21,943
on Serizawa.

551
00:39:21,985 --> 00:39:23,820
[footsteps approaching]

552
00:39:25,405 --> 00:39:26,990
[Kondo]
Toshi.

553
00:39:29,075 --> 00:39:32,120
That's not it, Yamanami.

554
00:39:33,288 --> 00:39:34,497
[Yamanami]
Huh?

555
00:39:35,790 --> 00:39:38,668
What exactly do you find wrong
with my plan?

556
00:39:40,712 --> 00:39:43,631
[Hijikata]
I'm saying we don't need
any damn schemes!

557
00:39:45,508 --> 00:39:47,135
We're going
to face them head-on,

558
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:48,636
and that's it.

559
00:39:49,637 --> 00:39:52,015
[sighs heavily]
[stick clatters]

560
00:39:53,683 --> 00:39:55,018
Honestly...

561
00:39:56,519 --> 00:40:00,607
When will you ever grow out
of this foolishness?

562
00:40:04,277 --> 00:40:06,613
This is... a power struggle

563
00:40:06,696 --> 00:40:10,074
between the Kondo
and the Serizawa factions.

564
00:40:11,701 --> 00:40:13,870
Do you even realize that?

565
00:40:16,539 --> 00:40:17,999
This isn't a game!

566
00:40:18,082 --> 00:40:20,793
[Hijikata]
You're the one
who doesn't get it!

567
00:40:22,712 --> 00:40:24,464
What did you just say?

568
00:40:25,965 --> 00:40:27,425
This is...

569
00:40:30,762 --> 00:40:33,514
isn't just some power struggle.

570
00:40:36,476 --> 00:40:38,978
Kamo is testing us.

571
00:40:42,440 --> 00:40:44,901
To see which of us
are true samurai.

572
00:40:48,446 --> 00:40:50,365
[scoffs]

573
00:40:50,406 --> 00:40:52,909
If we can't rise
to that challenge...

574
00:40:55,036 --> 00:40:57,789
then what's the point
of being samurai at all?

575
00:40:59,749 --> 00:41:03,211
You have no sense of your duty
as Vice-Commander.

576
00:41:03,252 --> 00:41:04,712
Are you willing
to destroy us all

577
00:41:04,754 --> 00:41:06,631
just to satisfy your emotions?

578
00:41:08,174 --> 00:41:09,968
[Kondo]
That's enough.

579
00:41:12,804 --> 00:41:15,515
What Yamanami's saying
is totally valid.

580
00:41:21,437 --> 00:41:22,814
Still...

581
00:41:24,691 --> 00:41:26,776
I'm with Toshi on this.

582
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:32,699
Kondo...

583
00:41:33,783 --> 00:41:36,577
Is a victory by scheming
a true victory?

584
00:41:39,831 --> 00:41:42,250
If we continue down that path,

585
00:41:42,333 --> 00:41:45,837
won't the Shinsengumi become
an empty shell of its ideals?

586
00:41:48,548 --> 00:41:50,967
No, but...

587
00:41:51,050 --> 00:41:53,928
[Kondo]
In order for the Shinsengumi
to get stronger,

588
00:41:55,847 --> 00:41:59,308
we will crush this internal
strife openly and head-on.

589
00:42:00,643 --> 00:42:02,103
And in doing so,

590
00:42:03,938 --> 00:42:07,108
we'll make a statement
to our men and to the world.

591
00:42:07,150 --> 00:42:10,069
[♪♪♪]

592
00:42:15,533 --> 00:42:16,951
So please.

593
00:42:19,328 --> 00:42:20,705
Yamanami.

594
00:42:23,207 --> 00:42:25,334
[sighs]

595
00:42:33,009 --> 00:42:34,177
Understood.

596
00:42:36,929 --> 00:42:38,139
But...

597
00:42:39,432 --> 00:42:41,100
on one condition.

598
00:42:43,144 --> 00:42:46,814
Kondo stays here.

599
00:42:49,358 --> 00:42:51,277
Should we fall in battle,

600
00:42:54,655 --> 00:42:57,784
you will annihilate any
enemy forces that get through.

601
00:43:00,036 --> 00:43:01,370
Do you agree?

602
00:43:01,454 --> 00:43:03,164
Yes,

603
00:43:04,499 --> 00:43:06,000
understood.

604
00:43:11,297 --> 00:43:12,715
Thank you.

605
00:43:18,679 --> 00:43:20,056
[Yamanami]
I...

606
00:43:21,891 --> 00:43:25,353
simply chose what I believe is
the best path in this situation.

607
00:43:25,394 --> 00:43:28,773
[♪♪♪]

608
00:43:35,947 --> 00:43:38,157
We move out in one hour.
[Hijikata] Okay.

609
00:43:38,241 --> 00:43:41,035
Vice-Commander Yamanami Keisuke
will be in command.

610
00:43:41,119 --> 00:43:43,871
May fortune favor you all
in battle.

611
00:43:43,955 --> 00:43:45,039
[all] Sir!

612
00:43:48,042 --> 00:43:51,003
OCTOBER 30, 1863

613
00:43:52,964 --> 00:43:58,052
[narrator]
Shimabara, usually alive
with noise as evening falls,

614
00:43:58,094 --> 00:44:02,056
was wrapped
in a deathly silence.

615
00:44:05,268 --> 00:44:07,854
Tonight would be
the final showdown.

616
00:44:07,895 --> 00:44:10,231
A rumor to that effect
was spreading,

617
00:44:10,314 --> 00:44:12,275
though from where, no one knew.

618
00:44:21,367 --> 00:44:25,288
[Oume playing shamisen]

619
00:44:45,725 --> 00:44:49,854
[♪♪♪]

620
00:44:59,614 --> 00:45:01,073
[chuckles softly]

621
00:45:08,623 --> 00:45:13,961
[Yoshiaki Dewa's "Chiruran
Shinsengumi Requiem" playing]
